parse: Verb - Future Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: From timios; to prize, i.e. Fix a valuation upon; by implication, to revere.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Father, (Heavenly) Father, ancestor, elder, senior. Apparently a primary word; a 'father'.
Or, than. A primary particle of distinction between two connected terms; disjunctive, or; comparative, than.
A mother. Apparently a primary word; a 'mother'.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To annul, make of no effect, cancel. To invalidate.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
From lego; something said; by implication, a topic, also reasoning or motive; by extension, a computation; specially, the Divine Expression.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
An instruction, tradition. From paradidomi; transmission, i.e. a precept; specially, the Jewish traditionary law.
